I built up a vgg-like model because it has strong abillity in classification. The accuracy of the validation set and the training set are both pretty good and the model is not underfitting or overfitting. I built 3 'blocks' of 2 convolutional layers each and use zero-padding to be able to build a deeper model. I set 32 filters for the first two convolutional layers, 64 for the next two layers and 128 for the last two layers. I set all filter with size 3*3 and set all maxpooling with size 2*2 which can reduce the number of inputs by a factor 4. To classify the images, I flatten the 4*4*128 feature map to a vector of size 2048 and set a dense and softmax layer at last. In order to prevent the model from overfitting, I set some dropout every MaxPooling and Dense layer.
